
/*
 * This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates the use of the [data.select] slot to filter data based on certain criteria. It utilizes the [strings.concat] slot to concatenate strings, the [embedding] slot to convert a float array to bytes, the [type] slot to specify a type, and the [math.subtract] slot to perform a subtraction operation. The [threshold] slot is used to set a threshold value for the selection process. The code effectively combines these slots to perform a data selection operation based on the specified type and threshold.
 * 
 * 1. [data.select] - Filters data based on specified criteria.
 * 2. [strings.concat] - Concatenates strings.
 * 3. [embedding] - Converts a float array to bytes.
 * 4. [type] - Specifies a type for the operation.
 * 5. [threshold] - Sets a threshold value for selection.
 * 6. [math.subtract] - Performs a subtraction operation.
 */
data.select:x:@strings.concat
   embedding:x:@floatArray2bytes
   type:x:@.arguments/*/type
   threshold:x:@math.subtract
